WEBVTT

00:02.210 --> 00:03.963
THIS IS

00:02.210 --> 00:03.963
PRETTY MUCH EVERY GAME.

00:03.963 --> 00:05.589
LET'S GO.

00:07.842 --> 00:10.928
[  INDISTINCT SHOUTING  ]

00:10.928 --> 00:12.721
DOES HE EVER WIN?

00:12.721 --> 00:14.139
YEAH, HE ALWAYS WINS.

00:15.015 --> 00:17.100
THIS IS MY DAD'S STRATEGY --

00:17.100 --> 00:20.729
HE'S A PUNCHING BAG

00:17.100 --> 00:20.729
WHO PUNCHES BACK.

00:20.729 --> 00:22.564
WHICH MAKES THE OTHER GUY

00:20.729 --> 00:22.564
FOCUS ON HIS HITS

00:22.564 --> 00:23.858
AND FORGET ABOUT HIS BALANCE.

00:23.858 --> 00:25.609
YEAH, LIKE TERRY O'REILLY.

00:25.609 --> 00:27.653
HE ACTUALLY

00:25.609 --> 00:27.653
USED TO BE PRETTY GOOD.

00:27.653 --> 00:30.405
IN THE JUNIORS, THEY SAID

00:27.653 --> 00:30.405
HE SKATED LIKE GUY LAFLEUR.

00:30.405 --> 00:31.615
THEN THEY SAW HIS RIGHT HOOK.

00:31.615 --> 00:34.159
THAT'S IT. ALL DONE.

00:31.615 --> 00:34.159
COME ON, GUYS.

00:34.159 --> 00:36.036
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

00:36.036 --> 00:37.287
WELL, THE CROWD LOVES HIM.

00:37.287 --> 00:39.665
YOU SHOULD SEE HIM

00:37.287 --> 00:39.665
AFTER THE GAME.

00:39.665 --> 00:42.250
HE COMES HOME

00:39.665 --> 00:42.250
ALL KINDS OF MESSED UP.

00:42.250 --> 00:43.460
HE GETS CONFUSED.

00:43.460 --> 00:44.628
HE SAYS THINGS

00:43.460 --> 00:44.628
THAT DON'T MAKE SENSE.

00:44.628 --> 00:46.005
LIKE WHAT THINGS?

00:46.005 --> 00:48.590
LIKE THE OTHER NIGHT,

00:46.005 --> 00:48.590
AFTER THE GAME,

00:48.590 --> 00:50.133
HE LOOKED AROUND THE CAR,

00:50.133 --> 00:52.260
AND HE ASKED ME

00:50.133 --> 00:52.260
WHERE MY MOM WAS.

00:52.260 --> 00:53.721
WHERE WAS SHE?

00:53.721 --> 00:55.806
UH, IT WAS A CAR ACCIDENT.

00:55.806 --> 00:58.058
THREE YEARS AGO.

00:58.058 --> 01:00.561
I'VE LOOKED ONLINE,

00:58.058 --> 01:00.561
AND ALL THE MEDICAL SITES

01:00.561 --> 01:03.898
SAY THE SAME THING

01:00.561 --> 01:03.898
ABOUT MY DAD'S SYMPTOM.

01:03.898 --> 01:06.233
IT'S CALLED CONCUSSION SYNDROME.

01:06.233 --> 01:09.904
IT CAN LEAD TO BRAIN DAMAGE

01:06.233 --> 01:09.904
AND EVEN DEATH.

01:09.904 --> 01:13.365
WHAT ABOUT HIS OWN DOCTORS?

01:09.904 --> 01:13.365
HE'S GOT TO BE CLEARED TO PLAY.

01:13.365 --> 01:15.492
THAT'S KIND OF THE PROBLEM.

01:15.492 --> 01:19.246
HE HAS TO GET EVALUATED

01:15.492 --> 01:19.246
BY THE DOCTORS ALL SEASON.

01:19.246 --> 01:20.581
HE'S GOT STACKS OF THESE PAPERS.

01:20.581 --> 01:24.418
"WE HAVE CONDUCTED

01:20.581 --> 01:24.418
A COMPLETE MEDICAL..."

01:24.418 --> 01:26.211
OKAY, SO,

01:24.418 --> 01:26.211
IT DOESN'T SAY ANYTHING

01:26.211 --> 01:28.296
ABOUT ANY SERIOUS HEAD TRAUMA.

01:28.296 --> 01:30.883
JUST BASIC CUTS,

01:28.296 --> 01:30.883
BRUISES, THINGS LIKE THAT.

01:30.883 --> 01:33.844
WHO IS THIS DR. MATSUDA --

01:30.883 --> 01:33.844
TEAM DOCTOR?

01:33.844 --> 01:35.220
YES.

01:35.220 --> 01:37.723
I KNOW IT SAYS HE HAD MRIs

01:37.723 --> 01:40.601
AND THE DOCTOR SAID HE WAS FINE,

01:40.601 --> 01:44.521
BUT I SEE MY DAD OFF THE RINK.

01:44.521 --> 01:47.482
AND HE IS NOT FINE, MR. FORD.

01:47.482 --> 01:48.943
THERE'S TWO GAMES

01:47.482 --> 01:48.943
LEFT IN THE SEASON.

01:48.943 --> 01:50.819
SO, AFTER THE SEASON,

01:48.943 --> 01:50.819
WHY DON'T YOU JUST

01:50.819 --> 01:52.613
BRING HIM TO A SPECIALIST

01:50.819 --> 01:52.613
AND GET ANOTHER OPINION?

01:52.613 --> 01:54.573
-I MEAN, SOMEBODY WHO WOULD --

01:52.613 --> 01:54.573
-IT'S NOT GONNA WORK.

01:54.573 --> 01:57.034
I'VE TRIED THAT A HUNDRED TIMES.

01:57.034 --> 01:58.493
HE WON'T DO IT.

01:58.493 --> 02:00.412
MY DAD THINKS

01:58.493 --> 02:00.412
HE'S INDESTRUCTIBLE.

02:00.412 --> 02:01.789
HE NEEDS HELP.

02:01.789 --> 02:05.292
YOU HELP PEOPLE

02:01.789 --> 02:05.292
WHO ARE BEING HURT, RIGHT?

02:06.710 --> 02:12.007
I NEED YOU TO SAVE MY DAD

02:06.710 --> 02:12.007
FROM HIMSELF.

02:13.801 --> 02:15.218
BUT I WANT TO SEE IT!

02:15.218 --> 02:16.804
I'M SERIOUS, PARKER. NO.

02:15.218 --> 02:16.804
IT'S NOT A TOY, OKAY?

02:16.804 --> 02:19.514
THIS IS A RARE-EARTH

02:16.804 --> 02:19.514
ELECTROMAGNET.

02:19.514 --> 02:21.391
IT'S VERY STRONG,

02:19.514 --> 02:21.391
VERY DANGEROUS.

02:21.391 --> 02:23.852
YOU EVER WONDER WHY

02:21.391 --> 02:23.852
NERDS HAVE NINE FINGERS?

02:23.852 --> 02:25.104
THAT'S WHY.

02:25.104 --> 02:27.147
OKAY?

02:25.104 --> 02:27.147
RIGHT NOW, IT'S INERT.

02:27.147 --> 02:28.857
BUT YOU FLIP THE SWITCH...

02:28.857 --> 02:30.776
[ ELECTROMAGNET BUZZES ]

02:32.569 --> 02:34.113
HMM.

02:34.113 --> 02:36.907
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

02:41.244 --> 02:43.122
OKAY, HARDISON.

02:43.122 --> 02:44.498
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

02:44.498 --> 02:46.708
OKAY.

02:44.498 --> 02:46.708
THE OREGON OTTERS.

02:46.708 --> 02:48.585
THEY'RE A MINOR-LEAGUE

02:46.708 --> 02:48.585
HOCKEY TEAM

02:48.585 --> 02:51.379
CURRENTLY IN THEIR FIFTH GAME

02:48.585 --> 02:51.379
OF A SEVEN-GAME PLAYOFF SERIES.

02:51.379 --> 02:52.714
UH...

02:52.714 --> 02:54.382
THERE GOES OUR MAN CRAIG MARKO.

02:54.382 --> 02:55.467
THAT'S DANNY'S POP.

02:55.467 --> 02:56.760
HE PLAYS WING FOR THE OTTERS,

02:56.760 --> 02:58.219
BUT, MORE IMPORTANTLY,

02:56.760 --> 02:58.219
HE'S AN ENFORCER.

02:58.219 --> 02:59.262
GOON.

02:59.262 --> 03:00.388
LIKE A BODYGUARD?

03:00.388 --> 03:01.473
-NO.

03:00.388 --> 03:01.473
-YEAH.

03:01.473 --> 03:02.766
WELL, YEAH.

03:02.766 --> 03:04.559
I MEAN, THE ENFORCERS EXIST

03:04.559 --> 03:06.311
TO PROTECT THE ELITE PLAYERS

03:06.311 --> 03:08.105
LIKE YOUR GRETZKYS,

03:06.311 --> 03:08.105
YOUR CROSBYS, AND EVERYTHING.

03:08.105 --> 03:09.481
THEY INTIMIDATE.

03:08.105 --> 03:09.481
THEY KEEP ORDER.

03:09.481 --> 03:11.150
WITHOUT THE ENFORCERS,

03:09.481 --> 03:11.150
WHAT WOULD YOU HAVE?

03:11.150 --> 03:12.776
-[ SCOFFS ]

03:11.150 --> 03:12.776
-I MEAN, YOU KNOW, THEY EXIST

03:12.776 --> 03:13.861
TO DO EXACTLY THAT.

03:13.861 --> 03:14.987
IT'S SORT OF LIKE THE FEAR

03:14.987 --> 03:16.237
OF HAVING TO FIGHT ONE OF THEM

03:16.237 --> 03:17.447
IS WHAT KEEPS EVERYTHING COOL.

03:17.447 --> 03:18.991
OH, SCHELLING'S THEORY

03:18.991 --> 03:20.742
OF RATIONAL DETERRENCE.

03:22.911 --> 03:24.287
THE COLD WAR?

03:24.287 --> 03:27.206
THAT'S ACTUALLY,

03:24.287 --> 03:27.206
TERRIFYINGLY, EXACTLY RIGHT.

03:27.206 --> 03:29.168
BUT IT DOESN'T APPLY HERE.

03:29.168 --> 03:30.377
GOONS EXIST FOR NOTHING MORE

03:30.377 --> 03:31.879
THAN A TWISTED,

03:30.377 --> 03:31.879
RITUALISTIC BATTLE

03:31.879 --> 03:33.672
THAT GRINDS

03:31.879 --> 03:33.672
THE ACTUAL HOCKEY TO A HALT

03:33.672 --> 03:35.423
SO THAT TWO THUGS

03:33.672 --> 03:35.423
CAN JUST SLUG IT OUT.

03:35.423 --> 03:36.800
WELL, IF YOU DIDN'T HAVE

03:35.423 --> 03:36.800
THE ENFORCERS,

03:36.800 --> 03:38.426
SUPERSTARS WOULDN'T EXIST.

03:38.426 --> 03:39.845
SO, THE OPPOSING TEAM

03:38.426 --> 03:39.845
WOULD JUST GO AFTER THE SNIPER.

03:39.845 --> 03:42.139
-THERE'S A JOB TO DO.

03:39.845 --> 03:42.139
-UH, YEAH.

03:42.139 --> 03:44.725
NOW, THIS IS PETE RISING.

03:42.139 --> 03:44.725
HE'S THE TEAM OWNER.

03:44.725 --> 03:46.393
DID A SMALL STINT IN THE NHL.

03:46.393 --> 03:48.353
HE BOUNCED AROUND A COUPLE

03:46.393 --> 03:48.353
RUSSIAN LEAGUES FOR A MINUTE.

03:48.353 --> 03:49.897
AND THEN HE INHERITS

03:48.353 --> 03:49.897
A TON OF MONEY,

03:49.897 --> 03:51.314
HE BUYS THE OREGON OTTERS,

03:51.314 --> 03:54.401
AND HE TURNS OUT

03:51.314 --> 03:54.401
TRIPLING THE TEAM'S REVENUE.

03:54.401 --> 03:57.696
AND HE DID IT BY TURNING

03:54.401 --> 03:57.696
THE ENFORCER, OR "GOON" FIGHTS,

03:57.696 --> 03:59.447
INTO A CIRCUS ATTRACTION.

03:59.447 --> 04:01.700
YOU SEE, HE MARKETED THE BRAWLS.

04:01.700 --> 04:04.912
HE CREATED, LIKE, A CULTURE

04:01.700 --> 04:04.912
WHERE GOING TO AN OTTER GAME

04:04.912 --> 04:06.997
MEANT HOCKEY WAS JUST

04:04.912 --> 04:06.997
SOMETHING THAT HAPPENED

04:06.997 --> 04:08.623
IN BETWEEN THE FIGHTS.

04:08.623 --> 04:11.376
LOOK. SEE ALL THESE DOTS

04:08.623 --> 04:11.376
RIGHT HERE?

04:11.376 --> 04:14.880
EVERY ONE OF THESE DOTS

04:11.376 --> 04:14.880
IS A CRAIG MARKO THROWDOWN.

04:14.880 --> 04:16.173
WHAT ARE THE RED ONES?

04:16.173 --> 04:17.216
THE RED ONES ARE FIGHTS

04:17.216 --> 04:18.550
THAT OTHER PLAYERS INITIATED.

04:18.550 --> 04:20.260
AND, AS YOU SEE,

04:18.550 --> 04:20.260
THERE AREN'T MANY OF THEM,

04:20.260 --> 04:22.679
BUT WHEN THEY DO HAPPEN,

04:20.260 --> 04:22.679
THEY HAPPEN IN CLUSTERS.

04:22.679 --> 04:25.306
FIGHTS IN EVERY PERIOD,

04:22.679 --> 04:25.306
EVEN ON POWER PLAYS?

04:25.306 --> 04:26.850
HOW WOULD YOU EVEN KNOW WHAT --

04:26.850 --> 04:28.602
I THOUGHT THIS GUY WAS LIKE

04:26.850 --> 04:28.602
A MINOR-LEAGUE HAMMER.

04:28.602 --> 04:29.978
YOU KNOW, LIKE -- LIKE --

04:28.602 --> 04:29.978
LIKE DAVE "THE HAMMER" SCHULTZ?

04:29.978 --> 04:31.188
WHO IS SHE?

04:31.188 --> 04:33.774
WHAT? OH. A GIRL

04:31.188 --> 04:33.774
CAN'T WATCH HOCKEY?

04:33.774 --> 04:35.442
WH-WHAT DID YOU STEAL?

04:35.442 --> 04:38.403
SOMETHING...HOCKEY-RELATED.

04:38.403 --> 04:40.614
A CERTAIN...TROPHY.

04:40.614 --> 04:42.199
NO, YOU DIDN'T.

04:40.614 --> 04:42.199
NO, NOT THE STANLEY CUP.

04:42.199 --> 04:43.366
UH-HUH.

04:43.366 --> 04:44.785
NO. I SAW IT

04:43.366 --> 04:44.785
LAST YEAR IN BOSTON.

04:44.785 --> 04:46.661
-NO, THAT WAS A FAKE.

04:44.785 --> 04:46.661
-IT WASN'T A FAKE.

04:46.661 --> 04:48.205
AND NOT A VERY GOOD ONE.

04:48.205 --> 04:50.082
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO. I'M SORRY.

04:48.205 --> 04:50.082
MY ENGRAVER WAS AWFUL.

04:51.917 --> 04:53.418
OKAY, SO, WHERE'S THE REAL ONE?

04:53.418 --> 04:55.087
I DON'T REMEMBER.

04:55.087 --> 04:56.880
DID -- NATE, THE...

04:56.880 --> 04:59.174
SO, DANNY, MARKO'S KID,

04:59.174 --> 05:00.842
THINKS THAT

04:59.174 --> 05:00.842
THE REAL MEDICAL FILES

05:00.842 --> 05:02.136
ARE BEING HIDDEN SOMEWHERE.

05:02.136 --> 05:03.762
SO WE GOT TO MAKE SURE

05:02.136 --> 05:03.762
THAT WE GET THOSE

05:03.762 --> 05:05.139
AND THAT MARKO DOESN'T FIGHT.

05:05.139 --> 05:07.015
HOW ARE WE GONNA

05:05.139 --> 05:07.015
KEEP THAT GUY FROM FIGHTING?

05:07.015 --> 05:08.600
THAT'S WHAT WE HAVE ELIOT FOR.

05:08.600 --> 05:11.853
YOU KNOW, TO, UH...FOR THE...

05:11.853 --> 05:15.107
OKAY, MY WA--

05:11.853 --> 05:15.107
ANYONE SEEN MY WATCH?

05:15.107 --> 05:17.025
-HARDISON?

05:15.107 --> 05:17.025
-HUH? WHAT?

05:17.025 --> 05:18.235
-MY WATCH.

05:17.025 --> 05:18.235
-I AIN'T SEEN NOTHING.

05:18.235 --> 05:19.569
WHY ARE YOU CALLING ME OUT?

05:22.156 --> 05:24.158
[ SIGHS ] LIKE I SAID,

05:24.158 --> 05:26.743
I'M ON MY WAY OUT,

05:24.158 --> 05:26.743
AND I DON'T HAVE TIME.

05:26.743 --> 05:28.996
SO IF YOU CAN, CALL MY OFFICE

05:26.743 --> 05:28.996
AND SCHEDULE AN APPOINTMENT,

05:28.996 --> 05:30.747
AND THEN WE CAN GO AHEAD

05:28.996 --> 05:30.747
AND TALK ABOUT THIS.

05:30.747 --> 05:32.833
I KNOW, BUT IT REALLY HURTS

05:30.747 --> 05:32.833
WHEN I DO THIS. OW!

05:32.833 --> 05:34.501
SEE? RIGHT THERE.

05:34.501 --> 05:36.837
WE COULD JUST GO TO YOUR OFFICE

05:34.501 --> 05:36.837
FOR LIKE A SECOND.

05:36.837 --> 05:39.714
OH, WANT SOME GUM?

05:39.714 --> 05:41.466
[ SIGHS ]

05:42.759 --> 05:46.138
NO, I MEAN, I DON'T HAVE TIME,

05:42.759 --> 05:46.138
MRS., UH...

05:46.138 --> 05:48.223
WHICH PLAYER IS YOUR HUSBAND?

05:48.223 --> 05:50.767
THE BIG ONE...

05:50.767 --> 05:52.435
WHO CAN SKATE.

05:54.479 --> 05:56.648
[ COUGHS ]

05:59.860 --> 06:02.403
[ SIGHS ]

06:08.493 --> 06:10.411
[ COMPUTER BEEPING ]

06:23.842 --> 06:25.302
IS THIS HIS ACTUAL MRI?

06:25.302 --> 06:27.762
YEAH. AND YOU DON'T

06:25.302 --> 06:27.762
WANT TO SEE HIS X-RAY.

06:27.762 --> 06:29.388
LOOKS LIKE

06:27.762 --> 06:29.388
A GAME OF PICK-UP STICKS.

06:30.265 --> 06:32.226
THIS SAYS,

06:30.265 --> 06:32.226
"INDICATIONS OF SWELLING

06:32.226 --> 06:33.685
ON THE BRAIN, POSSIBLE EDEMA."

06:33.685 --> 06:34.853
MM-HMM.

06:34.853 --> 06:36.980
RISING'S NOT JUST

06:34.853 --> 06:36.980
LETTING HIM PLAY,

06:36.980 --> 06:38.940
HE'S HIDING THIS

06:36.980 --> 06:38.940
TO MAKE HIM PLAY.

06:38.940 --> 06:41.026
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

06:38.940 --> 06:41.026
RIGHT.

06:42.652 --> 06:46.614
THE NEXT BLOW TO THE HEAD

06:42.652 --> 06:46.614
THAT CRAIG MARKO TAKES...

06:46.614 --> 06:49.534
COULD BE HIS LAST.

06:56.624 --> 06:58.377
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

07:03.798 --> 07:05.842
NICE SHOT.

07:05.842 --> 07:07.552
THE ICE IS CLOSED.

07:07.552 --> 07:11.014
THIS IS MY PRIVATE TIME TO

07:07.552 --> 07:11.014
CLEAR MY HEAD. I'M THE OWNER.

07:11.014 --> 07:12.557
PETE RISING, RIGHT?

07:12.557 --> 07:13.641
JEFF HANSEN.

07:13.641 --> 07:14.809
AGENT.

07:14.809 --> 07:16.811
BIG FAN

07:14.809 --> 07:16.811
OF YOU AND YOUR OTTERS.

07:16.811 --> 07:17.938
I HATE AGENTS.

07:17.938 --> 07:19.981
YOU AND ME BOTH, BROTHER.

07:19.981 --> 07:22.192
LISTEN, THE THING IS,

07:19.981 --> 07:22.192
I GOT THIS PLAYER, RIGHT?

07:22.192 --> 07:25.946
HE'S JUST OUT OF HIS CONTRACT,

07:22.192 --> 07:25.946
AND HE NEEDS A LITTLE EXPOSURE.

07:25.946 --> 07:27.239
CAN YOU HELP OUT?

07:27.239 --> 07:29.283
I'M AFRAID I CAN'T

07:27.239 --> 07:29.283
HELP YOU THERE, BROTHER.

07:30.700 --> 07:32.077
YOU DON'T EVEN

07:30.700 --> 07:32.077
WANT TO HEAR HIS STATS?

07:32.077 --> 07:33.078
[ SIGHS ]

07:34.037 --> 07:36.664
YOU THINK I SIGN PLAYERS

07:34.037 --> 07:36.664
'CAUSE OF THEIR STATS?

07:36.664 --> 07:38.917
PEOPLE DON'T COME HERE

07:36.664 --> 07:38.917
TO WATCH HOCKEY.

07:38.917 --> 07:41.253
THEY COME HERE TO SEE

07:38.917 --> 07:41.253
BLOODSTAINS ON THE ICE.

07:41.253 --> 07:43.088
SO WHY DON'T YOU CLEAR IT?

07:45.632 --> 07:48.593
TELL YOU WHAT --

07:45.632 --> 07:48.593
HOW ABOUT 1,000 BUCKS A PUCK?

07:48.593 --> 07:49.844
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

07:49.844 --> 07:51.596
SO, THIS ISN'T JUST

07:49.844 --> 07:51.596
HYPOTHETICAL?

07:51.596 --> 07:53.056
HEY, IF IT MAKES YOU NERVOUS...

07:53.056 --> 07:54.933
YOU KNOW, I USED TO

07:53.056 --> 07:54.933
PLAY PROFESSIONALLY.

07:54.933 --> 07:56.810
SURE -- EUROPE,

07:54.933 --> 07:56.810
CUP OF COFFEE IN THE NHL --

07:56.810 --> 07:58.812
YEAH, YOU PLAYED FOR A MINUTE.

07:58.812 --> 08:01.064
CUP OF COFFEE, HUH?

08:02.565 --> 08:04.109
LET'S SHOOT PUCKS FOR MONEY.

08:04.109 --> 08:06.527
YOU KNOW, MONEY -- IT'S JUST --

08:04.109 --> 08:06.527
IT'S SO OVERRATED.

08:06.527 --> 08:07.695
LET'S MAKE IT MORE INTERESTING.

08:07.695 --> 08:10.782
LET'S SAY, UH, 10 PUCKS, YEAH?

08:10.782 --> 08:14.161
IF I WIN, YOU PLAY MY GUY,

08:10.782 --> 08:14.161
YOU SIGN HIM.

08:14.161 --> 08:16.788
AND IF YOU WIN,

08:14.161 --> 08:16.788
YOU CAN HAVE MY BOAT,

08:16.788 --> 08:19.582
MY HOUSE, MY JET, MY WIFE.

08:19.582 --> 08:22.252
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:22.252 --> 08:24.212
LINE 'EM UP.

08:37.892 --> 08:39.019
[ METAL CLANGS ]

08:43.648 --> 08:46.109
[ GRUNTS ]

08:50.489 --> 08:52.366
[ METAL CLANGS ]

08:54.117 --> 08:55.952
[ BELL DINGS ]

08:58.372 --> 09:00.332
[ WHISTLES ]

09:07.839 --> 09:10.258
[ BOTH WHISTLING ]

09:13.094 --> 09:14.888
[ ELECTROMAGNET BEEPS ]

09:14.888 --> 09:16.223
[ GRUNTS ]

09:21.144 --> 09:22.603
OUCH.

09:24.939 --> 09:28.402
HEY, WHAT'S YOUR GUY'S NAME?

09:28.402 --> 09:30.237
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

09:30.237 --> 09:32.572
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,

09:32.572 --> 09:35.616
STRAIGHT FROM

09:32.572 --> 09:35.616
HIS RECORD-SETTING TURN

09:35.616 --> 09:38.619
IN THE NORTHERN CARIBOU

09:35.616 --> 09:38.619
LEAGUE...

09:38.619 --> 09:40.121
WHAT LEAGUE?

09:40.121 --> 09:43.875
...LET'S GIVE

09:40.121 --> 09:43.875
AN OREGON OTTERS WELCOME TO...

09:43.875 --> 09:46.086
JACQUES LaBERT!

10:00.683 --> 10:04.312
IT'S ACTUALLY PRONOUNCED "JACK."

10:15.449 --> 10:18.452
WELCOME BACK TO GAME SIX

10:15.449 --> 10:18.452
OF THIS SEVEN-GAME SERIES

10:18.452 --> 10:22.038
BETWEEN THE OREGON OTTERS

10:18.452 --> 10:22.038
AND THE RENO FREEZE.

10:22.038 --> 10:24.291
LET'S GO, MARKO.

10:22.038 --> 10:24.291
YOU AND ME. COME ON.

10:24.291 --> 10:25.542
LOOKS LIKE BOWMAN

10:24.291 --> 10:25.542
IS TAUNTING MARKO AGAIN.

10:25.542 --> 10:27.294
OH, YEAH? YEAH?

10:25.542 --> 10:27.294
YOU WANT SOME, MAN?

